## Rule: Range Inputs with Alpine.js Bindings

- Use `x-model` for real-time updates of min/max length values.
- Display current value with `x-text` or `:value`.
- Bind both to visible UI and hidden form field (if using HTMX submission).
- Use Flowbite‚Äôs `range` input styling, but manage state with Alpine.

### Example

```html
<div x-data="{ min: 4, max: 8 }">
  <label>Min Length: <span x-text="min"></span></label>
  <input type="range" x-model="min" min="1" max="32" class="w-full h-2 bg-gray-200 rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer">

  <label>Max Length: <span x-text="max"></span></label>
  <input type="range" x-model="max" min="1" max="32" class="w-full h-2 bg-gray-200 rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer">

  <input type="hidden" name="min_length" :value="min">
  <input type="hidden" name="max_length" :value="max">
</div>
```
